label: 1816-1817 Draft of Frankenstein, from MS. Abinger c.56 and MS. Abinger c.57

metadata.label: Description
metadata.value: Derivative IIIF Manifest for Bodleian Libraries MS. Abinger c.56 and MS. Abinger c.57, containing Mary Wollstonecraft Shelley’s Draft of Frankenstein, 1816-1817. This manifest sequences the images based on the linear sequence of the novel, as suggested by the Shelley-Godwin Archive. Not shown are pages unrelated to the Frankenstein draft. | Bodleian MS. Abinger c.56 (formerly designated Dep. 477/1) consists of 62 leaves originally bound in Notebook A, one of two now disbound notebooks in which Mary W. Shelley (MWS) drafted the two-volume version of Frankenstein. The draft in c.56 runs from the beginning to the end of Volume I, concluding just as the Creature is about to begin his tale to Victor. Bodleian MS. Abinger c.57 (formerly designated Dep. 534/1) consists of 94 leaves, of which 18 were originally bound in Notebook A and 76 in Notebook B, the notebooks in which Mary W. Shelley (MWS) drafted the two-volume version of Frankenstein. The draft in c.57 includes the entirety of Volume II, Chapters 1-18, and was written in Fall 1816. | Additional information: See http://shelleygodwinarchive.org
